Looking beyond the status quo of the modern rock music of today, Earshot&#039;s 
third studio album, aptly titled "The Silver Lining", marks the start of what 
some believe is sure to be the beginning of a new and changing modern rock 
world of tomorrow. No doubt, that in the 48 minutes of listening to the bevy 
of infectiously memorable tracks, one can only describe this 11 song collection 
as a very cleverly crafted, re-defined and re-designed approach to their 
genre with a plethora of sonically raw and defining moments. Tracks such as 
"MisSunderstood", "Closer", "Pushing To Shove", "Wasted", "Don&#039;t Hate Me" 
and "Sometimes" are sure to please the Earshot faithful, and will undoubtedly 
serve to quickly convert new fans by songs with a penchant for massive 
hooks and loud guitars.
